#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat << 'EOF'
GitHub content: skip page fetches (WebFetch, curl, gh api contents reads); hooks deny them. Go straight to:
- Repository files, wikis, gists: clone, then read; `git show <ref>:<path>` for a file at a ref.
- PRs: `gh pr view <n> --repo <owner>/<repo> --comments`, `gh pr diff <n>` for changes.
- Issues: `gh issue view <n> --comments`. Discussions: `gh discussion view <n>`.
- Releases: `gh release view <tag>`, assets via `gh release download <tag>`.
- CI runs: `gh run view <id> --log-failed`. Search: `gh search <code|commits|issues|prs|repos> <query>`.
- Other API reads: `gh api <path>` (authenticated; anonymous fetches are capped at 60/hour).
EOF
